759	\begin{remark}[Iter-046+ remaining producer-instance assembly]
760	  Iter-045 closes step (2) of the iter-044 four-step plan (identifying $(\Sheaf.\Gamma).\mathtt{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ with $\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,(\Gamma(C, \top))$ as $k$-modules — via the iter-006 evaluation simp lemma + \lstinline{Sheaf.ΓNatIsoSheafSections}). Iter-046+ closes step (1): the constant-sheaf / global-sections $\LinearEquiv$ between the two sides of \lstinline{constantSheafΓAdj.homEquiv}. This step is the substantive one: Mathlib has \lstinline{Adjunction.homAddEquiv} (lifting $\mathtt{homEquiv}$ to an additive equivalence under $F.\mathtt{Additive}$) but no $\LinearEquiv$ analogue. Constructing the linearised version requires either project-local $\Functor.\Additive$ instances on $\mathtt{constantSheaf}$ and $\Sheaf.\Gamma$ plus a manual check of $k$-scalar compatibility, or a direct construction of forward/backward $k$-LinearMaps.
761	\end{remark}
