777	\section{Mathlib gap}
778	
779	After Section~\ref{sec:scheme_toModuleKSheaf} is implemented, this chapter has no remaining Mathlib gap. The construction reuses only the following established Mathlib pieces:
780	
781	\begin{itemize}
782	  \item \lstinline{CategoryTheory.HasSheafify}, \lstinline{CategoryTheory.HasExt.standard}, and the abelian/$\Linear\,k$ enrichment on $\Sheaf(J, \ModuleCat\,k)$ (verified by \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probes; underlies Sections~\ref{sec:moduleK_prereqs}–\ref{sec:moduleK_ext}).
783	  \item \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.\Gamma SpecIso}, \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Hom.app}, \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.presheaf} (existing Mathlib API for the structure morphism and the structure-sheaf restriction maps).
784	  \item \lstinline{Algebra.compHom} / \lstinline{RingHom.toAlgebra} (algebra-from-ring-map).
785	  \item \lstinline{CategoryTheory.Presheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheaf_forget} (concrete-category sheaf criterion; transfers the sheaf condition between $\CommRingCat$ and $\ModuleCat\,k$).
786	\end{itemize}
787	
788	Nothing genuinely new is required from Mathlib. The iter-006 plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe verifies the full $\sim$80-LOC construction end-to-end against Mathlib \texttt{b80f227}.
